The Carlton, Hofferkamp and Jenks Cares Program


Our community matters to us.

 
Our Story


Giving back to the community has been an integral part of our company from the inception.  
The Carlton, Hofferkamp and Jenks Cares Program launched in January 2016, a year round giving program created solely for the purpose of strengthening our community through community service and donations.
Our Cares Program is an organic extension of our commitment to our clients and now extends to the community.  We believe small charitable efforts can have a great impact in the local community and we are committed to helping ours thrive.

 








Small acts of kindness
when multiplied by millions
can transform the world.

 






Our Hope


Our goal is to proactively seek and create local grassroots initiatives and nurture community collaboration to strengthen our community, the foundation of The Carlton, Hofferkamp and Jenks Cares Program.
Our Cares Program encourages community partnerships dedicated to making positive and meaningful contributions throughout our community.
We will consider employee volunteer time, a financial or in-kind contribution to local nonprofit 501 (c) (3) organizations typically with modest budgets, direct community impact and supports the cornerstones of our community:
Education
|
Health and Wellness
|
Hunger Relief
|
The Environment

 


Our community matters to us.

 








