 HOW WE CAREWhat Keeps You Up At Night?


We invite you to a complimentary consultation – no selling, no gimmicks, just straight talk to help guide you on your path to financial success.

 





FAQ


Where are my assets held?



Carlton, Hofferkamp & Jenks does not take custody of clients assets. We partner with Charles Schwab to serve as a custodian of our client’s assets.  All client monies and assets are held at Charles Schwab.  If a client would like us to manage their money but would like to use a different custodian, we will consider the request.

 

How often do I get statements?



Monthly statements are produced and mailed (physically or electronically) from Charles Schwab, not from Carlton, Hofferkamp and Jenks.  In addition to the monthly statements, we send out quarterly summary and performance statements which we outsource from a third party vendor, PORTFOLIOSERVICES.

 

How do I open an account?



Just contact us.  We will do all the work for you.  We will help you set up your Charles Schwab account and after our discovery process, which will include our management agreement, we’ll  begin to manage your account.

 

What if I already have an account at Charles Schwab?



It’s simple.  All you have to do is authorize Carlton, Hofferkamp and Jenks to manage your account by simply signing our management agreement form and also the corresponding Charles Schwab designation form.

 

How do I log on to my Charles Schwab account?



Visit this link

 

Do you have a privacy policy?



Clients and prospective clients should know that we take privacy and confidentiality very serious.  Feel free to read our Privacy Policy.

 

Read our Disclosure Statement



Disclosure Statement

 

How do I get a copy of your ADV form?



Copies of our ADV II form are available upon request at any time by prospective clients and clients alike.  
Request an ADV II using our Contact Form.


 

How do I sign up for daily market updates?



Sign Up for Daily Market Updates

 

